RAPIST and killer Matome Maphutha will serve two life sentences and five more years in jail for the kidnap, rape and murder of Lethabo Ngobeni (11).Lethabo’s lifeless body was found in Maphutha’s house in Refilwe, Cullinan in Tshwane in May. This angered community members who vandalised Maphutha’s house and broke all the windows.Maphutha (45) was arrested in Bronkhorstspruit.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>He was sentenced on Thursday at the North Gauteng High Court.Reacting to the sentencing, Lethabo’s uncle, Andries Ngobeni (44), said the family was still in pain.“We are happy about the outcome of the case, even though we will never see our Lethabo,” he said.Andries said they were shocked that Maphutha’s family never visited them to find out how they were coping after their niece was murdered.He thanked their neighbours for all their support and the police for their tireless efforts in making sure Maphutha rots in jail. Andries also thanked churches for their prayers and Chokoe Primary School, where Lethabo was a pupil, for its support.Tshwane East commander Major-General Andre Wiese applauded Constable Thabiso Ramalatsi of Tshwane East family violence, child protection and sexual offences unit for his professionalism during the investigation.He said it was Constable Ramalatsi’s hard work and presentation of evidence to the court that led to the successful prosecution, conviction and sentencing of Maphutha.